title.narrative: Number of participants in active labor market programs inserted into jobs, including in the occupational field for which they are trained
Number of job seekers, as reported by the LFS, served by the National Employment Service
Labor market information (LMI) system in place and two reports on labor market situation and trends published

target.value: MLSPP publishes a comprehensive statistical and analytical report on labor market situation and developments

actual.value: A Model PIMS developed, tested, and staff trained; One report on Azerbaijan labor market prepared; Data being collected but noregular reports produced due to lack of capable and trained staff for further implementation

title.narrative: Computerized record keeping in all MLSPP and its affiliated agencies offices.

baseline.value: Except for the TSA, automation only partial and only in some parts of the system.

target.value: Implementation on schedule/MIS completed as planned

actual.value: Information system including computerized record keeping in the MLSPP and its affiliated agencies completed as planned

title.narrative: 30 new module training programs developed and in use and three new module training centers fully functional

baseline.value: Insufficient to meet demand; the number of modules limited.

target.value: 100% modular programs developed; training takes place accordingly

actual.value: Exceeds the target - 43 modular training programs (out of 30 planned) developed and in use; new training centers functional(training being provided).

title.narrative: Central and three regional occupational safety laboratories modernized and fully functional and two reports on work and occupational safety published

baseline.value: Labs in very poor conditions, barely operational

actual.value: New central laboratory never established; building never constructed; the issue of premises remain unresolved; equipment modernizedand occupational safety function performed, labs in better conditions but not as envisaged under the project; One report published.

title.narrative: Targeting mechanism and implementation procedures adjusted after each round of monitoring survey

baseline.value: Legislation on TSA was adjusted after 2008 survey

target.value: Adjustments take place based on 2011 monitoring survey

actual.value: A Decree on TSA signed by the president on February 23, 2015

title.narrative: Operations guidelines and manuals for a new menu of ALMPs prepared and in use
Central and regional Career Counseling Centers operational

target.value: Career counseling activities implemented; Report issued; evaluation report issued.

actual.value: Career counseling activities designed and implemented; relevant legislation revised; Career guidance services provided andevaluation reports prepared on an ad hoc basis.

title.narrative: MIS system generates intended reports on programs, participants and flow of funds and feeds into M&E activities

actual.value: MIS generates intended reports – culture of data usage by business processes and decision making introduced.

title.narrative: 200 occupational standards, based on ISCO-88/ISCO-08, and 100 training standards developed and in use

actual.value: Exceeded target - 245 occupational and 200 training standards developed and in use

title.narrative: Automated, up to date information on nationwide vacancies available in all local NES offices

target.value: 75% of new jobs advertised through NES

actual.value: COMPLETED (more than 75% of new jobs advertised through NES)
